description.narrative:
This is a core funding to the Cooperation Committee for Cambodia,&nbsp;the largest&nbsp;umbrella organization in Cambodia focusing on establishing a strong and capable civil society, cooperating and responsive to Cambodia and global development challenge. The CCC&rsquo;s services and roles include coordination, capacity building, research and learning, networking and advocacy with nation-wide geographic coverage.
The new Governance Hub Programme (phase 3) consists of two main goals:
1) Enhanced effectiveness and impact of civil society organizations (CSOs)&nbsp;
2) Improved enabling environment for CSOs
The project is expected to delivered the following outcomes:&nbsp;
1) Increased capacity of CSOs for innovative response to development challenges
2) Improved multi-stakeholder partnership in policy development and effective development cooperation at all levels; and
3) Strengthened active participation of CCC members and innovative services of CCC secretariat.
Rights holders who directly benefits from the work of the CCC are estimated about 8,115 staff members of more than 170 civil society organizations with networks across Cambodia including grassroots and community-based organizations, reaching directly to almost two millions total population in Cambodia.&nbsp;
The CCC addresses the country&rsquo;s current democracy challenge where civil society needs to be present to exercise their active roles in various multi-stakeholder platforms on various development agendas, particularly under the new Sustainable Development Goals together with rights holders on the ground.
